 that for `testImplementation`, I have 2.11, which creates a compileClasspath conflict favoring 2.13. I confirm that if ScalaCompile infers from compileClasspath, then it can compile fine. It looks like my current build is leading to runtime 2.13, which isn't intended.\n\n**Inspecting Scala versions**\n\nI’m checking how scalac works with different Scala versions at compile time, particularly 2.11 and 2.13. It looks like it creates a scalaClasspath from classpath entries, which seems likely. I need a minimal test source compatible with 2.11, and my current TrieMapTest uses Scala Option which may reference scala.Some$.MODULE$ at runtime for 2.11. However, I’m a bit concerned because the signatures for the TrieMap methods might differ between versions. I'll inspect them using javap for clarity.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0deada2f5b146a450169f8fb6cad308195aa09a1056d2765d8\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-PuNsiUS-nPJdsCo7lnb5a5LZOqQ7epUwPIuG35SANnG87Wq5YWUYOfaRy1dwE_lwQjhcYe8WUgg8iodRSN_eu80YhErWLZTow6IyKrj-jh6kyabVLod_0AGeAD4gCLDoaxR1TCXR4xX9DB1SJ9AdacXgqISFuyAqwKqyaSRR4w_Qxbw24IMKve2ScfSi6qJ8tcyEmoOKhcyJGPfWxSvi20wNFj_qMk05qXA3YgttEYP9RwaAy6ZLOPTh5ML113zzXz0xaIXyUZeWYN9_FJmc6YfKH_3H42bgy27XFQKlwD8tERxUtQFjb16V7qHN_F_8o1U2kah3K1pigmWKghtVtEP5Tb4k8yYq3UNRn8cyreBNbSGIOrsf07TqP8iyJz2SjjvCMre9EHOWD4hvPUYpn0x0iEHnQQv0QnGYx6q5mianCRDe5WRyxUZ_p_naTFlYBitzssD1-GH5mY67QK0iC1_Vmxzu6vOIna8FVSWIJbw6X91bBCK3ijh08PbrYiQsXFsMNA_51TruLB_yArSePJSkUMwh9oeI-9t8cUwobj_izJ0494bFqCt2RaYhAVAaEeNjCIV3LZ6t5pQPuU2iEkFoDwnlNSxdnDHO1kBxvR0SldvaPxe0xWa5D4rmewVSK-ciVt-TO5uvIUDpDXe9h0ihinLrb1wnk07fzWclqZGJ59_rB_S6khTAK0Ovhz_6zdnm18MQyqsnjGUQgjn1g8Xpc4ZDBzpDF-ctXyLuviXOBqYITEndCN1sidQ5xhSITasotQVMqOfFLBY7nPWM5nVM5QYVd4ygSk_mEXumDETiMjEKaAwE8tNjWbkNfFiykJn6IZVHsDvZt2ZO9I5xPzRt0wB90oXpABlwQxqpAULp5zC1xkFrG2hLJWKCo164uVnKwEYdU0L5eIB_x3nEuD183k83oprwbuzTYvxet71wgIInp2T8i7ztgcOG3sZEmR9E3Pj83YizRZqpjuo1jiUc7SBO_nssGLIjebb70r6DYZr6wkgS9NZbaiGTDydkQhYhhhQQ2dGiyMW_MzvI51X2B2